# Security Incident Report

## Incident Summary
A series of failed authentication attempts were detected in Windows Security logs. The pattern indicates a possible brute-force attack attempt.

## Log Evidence
Event ID: 4625  
Source IP: 192.168.1.25  
Number of Attempts: 40 failed login attempts within 3 minutes.

## Indicators of Compromise
- Suspicious IP address
- Repeated login attempts
- Targeted administrator account

## Analysis
The repeated authentication failures from a single IP address indicate automated brute-force login attempts.

## Severity Level
Medium

## Recommended Response
- Block suspicious IP address
- Enable account lockout policy
- Monitor authentication logs for continued attack activity
